# Agent QA Project Memory (`.agent-qa/`)

Runtime persistent memory for QA runs. Format contract: @.agent-qa/structure.md. Content: @.agent-qa/memory.md.

## Chunk types (`MemoryChunkType` — planned domain contract)

`project`, `route`, `flow`, `semantic_locator`, `scenario`, `known_issue`, `runtime_learning`

Each section in `memory.md` must include metadata:

```markdown
## Section title
<!-- type: route | id: ROUTE-001 -->
Content here...
```

## Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `memory.md` | Searchable project knowledge (BM25 index planned) |
| `structure.md` | Conventions for sections and chunk types |
| `run-history.jsonl` | One JSON event per line (run summaries) |

## Rules

- Version in Git; **never** literal passwords, tokens, API keys, or env values
- Reference auth via config/env names only (e.g. `usernameEnv`, `passwordEnv`)
- Each chunk `id` must be **unique** — validated by `npm run validate:agent-config`
- Keep chunks focused and independently useful for search
- Sync stable learnings from `.cursor/memory/` when they help QA execution
- `TaskMemoryService` is ephemeral — do not write run-scratch state into `memory.md`

## Future services (not yet in `src/`)

`MemoryChunker`, `BM25MemoryIndex`, `MemorySearchService` — see `tasks-clickup/PRJ-11315/`.
